sample.title: No Nvidia Chips Needed! Amazon‚Äôs New AI Data Center For Anthropic Is Truly Massive
sample.description:
On 1,200 acres in Indiana, Amazon‚Äôs biggest AI data center is now operational, with half a million AWS Trainium2 chips entirely devoted to powering OpenAI rival Anthropic. Just over a year ago, the whole site was nothing but dirt and cornfields. Seven buildings are operating now, and once complete, the site will have around 30 buildings and consume some 2.2 gigawatts of power. CNBC went to the small town of New Carlisle, Indiana, to talk to locals who are worried about the impact on their community and electric bills - and to get a first ever on-camera tour inside what Amazon‚Äôs calling the largest cluster of non-Nvidia chips in the world. We also sat down with AWS CEO Matt Garman and Anthropic CPO Mike Krieger for more details on the partnership.

Air India crash sole survivor 'luckiest man' alive, but also suffering | BBC News
sample.description:
The sole survivor of the Air India plane crash, which killed 241 people on board, has said he feels like the "luckiest man" alive, but is also suffering physically and mentally.
 
Viswashkumar Ramesh walked away from the wreckage of the London-bound flight in Ahmedabad.
 
He said it was a "miracle" he escaped but told how he has lost everything, as his younger brother Ajay died in the crash in June.
 
Since returning to his home in Leicester, Mr Ramesh has struggled with post-traumatic stress disorder, his advisers said, and has been unable to speak to his wife and four-year-old son.
